body: Hi, can I work on this? Looking to make my first open source contribution.

Hi, thank you very much for stepping up.

It would be great to have you help. You can pick one function and submit a first pull request. It's good to iterate from a simple contribution in order to learn the process.
Alright thanks. I'll be working on DatetimeEncoder.fit.
For some reason when I try to do numpydoc validation it exits with no errors but collects 0 items. Should I change the name of the file/function to begin with "test"?
Having trouble doing numpydoc validation bc of issue mentioned above. Can someone please help?

Hi @alexdt1982
Thanks for the heads up, it was an issue with the test itself. I fixed it and it should work now!
Don't forget to fetch the commits added in the master branch (`pull master`). I've also updated the comment above :)

Validated docstring for DatetimeEncoder.fit. but getting this issue when I try to commit @LilianBoulard @GaelVaroquaux. Seems to be an issue with pre-commit or anaconda.
![Screenshot (143)](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/77065772/190481020-7f1b9728-ee2f-496d-a274-e99dc5dd64ad.png)

Yes, this is a Windows-specific issue, but both Gaël and I work on linux-based distributions. Search for solutions on Stack Overflow, you'll most likely find help there. If you have issues related to dirty_cat, we'll be able to help, but this is not one, sorry!
No worries, I resolved the issue. Will create a PR soon.
